<br>
Guess what? You're a fucking moron. OPEC decides the prices of oil by changing their production rates. If they triple the amount of oil entering the world market the price will drop drastically, if they half what they are letting out the price will sky rocket. These last price increases were caused because opes lowered their production by something like 10%, imagine what would happen if they cut it in half? As with everything the price is ultimately decided by the consumer and not the producer, however with a resourcec like oil which is needed by most of the world the produce ends up playing a major role. It's all basic Supply and Demand type situations.<br>
<br>
Constant Demand + Constant Supply = Constant Price<br>
<br>
Increase in Demand + Constant Supply = Increase in Price<br>
<br>
Constant Demand + Increase in Supply = Decerase in Price<br>
<br>
Or in the case of oil:<br>
<br>
Constant Demand + Decrease in Supply= Increase in Price<br>
<br>
<br>
